HEADWORD: Pretex
<hw>Pre*tex"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praetexere</ets>. See <er>Pretext</er>.]</ety> <def>To frame; to
devise; to disguise or excuse; hence, to pretend; to declare
falsely.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

